history.text: hellos
hello
Have you ever seen this movie before? it is a classic
would you name the movie..?
Its Jaws, directed by Steven Spielberg
Steven is a incredible director
how is it with respect to its story..?
how interesting did you find its story line..?

Its a pretty good story line. The story is about a giant man-eating great white shark who attacks any beach goer. With so many attacks happening the police chief decides its his responsibility
 to hunt down this giant beast.
sounds goodi...
good*
the movie originally came out in 1975 as well.
is it an animated movie..?
for the most part the movie is real life but there are animated effects that really make all the difference in the action scenes of the movie.
so is this a sequel or remake to one released before..?
who are the actors playing different roles...?
its the first movie for this story line

the cast is roy scheider who is the chief in the movie, then there is rober shaw who plays a main character, then there is richard dreyfuss who plays as a main character, and Lorraine Gary who plays a main character as well
the cast looks good
is the movie thriller..?
are you familiar with any of these actors?
yes the movie is a thriller and received a 97% rating on rotten tomatoes
i know roy scheider and heard of rober shaw
can kids watch it..?

I think that kids should be able to watch it, although it is a pretty action packed movie. Maybe if your kids are sensitive to scary situations it would not be a good movie to show, but I think I would be able to watch it as a kid.
does it involve violence..?
There is definitely some violence as the movie is about a man eating great white shark. There is also violence while hunting this beast of a sea creature down.
